
.TH man 1 "26 July 2021" "1.0" "_printf man page"

.SH NAME
_printf - prints a stream of characters to the standard output

.SH SYNOPSIS

#include <stdarg.h>

#include <unistd.h>

#include <stddef.h>

int _printf(const char *format, ...);

.SH DESCRIPTION

The function _printf a custom function built for the alx software engineering program. It is supposed to have a near similar functionality as the printf function from the standard library.

Format Specfiers

d, i -------- integer

c ----------- character

f ----------- floating point number

o ----------- an octal number

b ----------- a binary number

x, X -------- a hexadecimal number

s ----------- a string

u ----------- an unsigned number

p ----------- pointer

r ----------- reversed string

R ----------- Rot13'ed string

Flag characters are -, 0, +, (space), #

Length modifiers are l, h

Precision and width is also handled

